CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper August 30, 1947, pg. 10, reads: "Pittsburgh Weddings - Repeating marriage vows recently where the couples pictured above... third: Mr. and Mrs. Edward Jackson... - All photos by Harris." Portion of accompanying article reads: "Perry - Jackson. Miss Evelyn Perry [illegible]... daughter of Mr. and Mrs... [il.] of Elizabeth, Pa... Edward Jackson... Mrs. R. K.... following..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of two men, including groom Edward Jackson, and three women, including bride Evelyn Perry holding large bouquet with gladiolus, posed in interior with floral wallpaper and lace curtains
